### --- RFP COLLABORATION (in-memory) — base path /rfp-collab ---
### Users: jordan@juno / pm123 (Jordan Mitchell, PM)
###        aiyana@juno, chayton@juno, talise@juno, kiona@juno / aud123 (Auditors)
### After login, use: Authorization: Bearer <token>  (token = user id from response)
###

### C1. Login (Proposal Manager)
POST http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jordan@juno",
  "password": "pm123"
}

###

### C2. Create workspace + questions (replace Bearer with PM token from C1)
POST http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/create-workspace
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer user_pm_1

{
  "title": "Sample Cloud RFP",
  "document": "Section L: Technical volume required. Past performance: 3 references.",
  "questions": [
    { "number": 1, "text": "Describe your cloud security architecture." },
    { "number": 2, "text": "List three comparable past performances." }
  ]
}

###

### C3. List auditors (PM)
GET http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/auditors
Authorization: Bearer user_pm_1

###

### C4. Assign question (use workspace id + question id from C2 response body)
POST http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/assign-question
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer user_pm_1

{
  "workspaceId": "REPLACE_WS_ID",
  "questionId": "REPLACE_Q_ID",
  "auditorUserId": "user_aud_2"
}

###

### C5. Auditor dashboard — Chayton Bitsui (user_aud_2)
GET http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/auditor-dashboard/user_aud_2
Authorization: Bearer user_aud_2

###

### C6. AI draft answer (auditor; needs OPENAI_API_KEY)
POST http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/draft-answer-ai
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer user_aud_2

{
  "workspaceId": "REPLACE_WS_ID",
  "questionId": "REPLACE_Q_ID"
}

###

### C7. Submit answer
POST http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/submit-answer
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer user_aud_2

{
  "workspaceId": "REPLACE_WS_ID",
  "questionId": "REPLACE_Q_ID",
  "answerText": "Our organization implements zero-trust architecture with continuous monitoring..."
}

###

### C8. Review answer (PM) — decision: approve | reject | request_changes
POST http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/review-answer
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer user_pm_1

{
  "workspaceId": "REPLACE_WS_ID",
  "questionId": "REPLACE_Q_ID",
  "decision": "approve",
  "comment": "Looks good for volume 1."
}

###

### C9. Activity logs (PM)
GET http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/logs/REPLACE_WS_ID
Authorization: Bearer user_pm_1

###

### C10. Quarterly review items (PM or assigned auditor)
GET http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/quarterly-review/REPLACE_WS_ID
Authorization: Bearer user_aud_2

###

### C11. Quarterly review update (auditor)
POST http://localhost:3000/rfp-collab/quarterly-review
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer user_aud_2

{
  "workspaceId": "REPLACE_WS_ID",
  "reviewItemId": "REPLACE_QR_ITEM_ID",
  "status": "needs_update"
}